New tools for car repair
In these days of storms and accidents, not only do car workshops win.
Every day thousands of cars that have suffered a crash are towed to a workshop, where an expert must evaluate the damage suffered and what the cost of repair will be.
No damage is the same, and calculating parts costs and labor time can be a long and complicated job.
Calculate manually the cost of a repair of between 20,000 and 30,000 euros, including parts and workmanship, can take two or three hours.
Instead, with the support of the latest computer tools, it would be a matter of minutes.
That is why almost 100% of experts use this type of systems.
The providers of services and solutions for damage assessment and maintenance are dedicated to collecting the information provided by the manufacturers, and then elaborate it and offer it to their customers in the form of a useful tool.
In Spain, Audatex, of the North American group Solera, is the leading firm; 80% of the valuations are made with its products.
The other firms competing in the field of appraisal and information-processing tools on the sector are GtMotive and Eurotax.
Working with the data provided by manufacturers is far from simple.
According to Eduardo Vel<0xC3><0xA1>zquez, commercial director of Audatex, in Spain they work with 63 manufacturers and importers, and each of them provides them with the information in different formats.
In addition, the amount of data to be processed continues to increase, to the point that in the last five years more versions, variants and motorizations have been released than in the previous fifteen.
As soon as a new car comes to market, these companies start working.
It is a very arduous task, because you have to catalog each of the thousands of parts of the vehicle and enter its price.
In addition, from each model a "smart" graphic image is made where different parts of tourism can be "stuck".
If it is a bulky model, the job can be ready in a week if the process goes very fast.
If you are a minority car, it may take three or four months. Currently, Audatex has complete information about 99.2% of cars sold in Spain.
Among the most exclusive models have information about Porsche, but not Ferrari or Lamborghini, for example.
As for the mobile fleet that circulates, they exceed 99%.
To carry out the documentation work and the development of the databases, Audatex has eight centers spread around the world (Spain, France, Germany, USA, Brazil, Mexico, China and Japan), and each of them is specialized in specific brands.
The national headquarters is in Alcobendas (Madrid).
There, more than a hundred technicians (usually mechanical experts) work simultaneously with three computer screens.
Audatex invests <0xE2><0x82><0xAC>90 million annually in developing these databases.
Every month, 2.5 million data is included, and customers receive updates every two days.
The elaboration of this huge flow of information allows these companies to give them different uses and offer various products.
The most common use is focused on repair and maintenance, but depending on which countries there are also tools for managing scrap parts or to calculate the venal or residual value of a car.
The only company that has a guide that informs about the value of used in Spain is Eurotax.
Audatex does not offer it in our country, but it does in the United States.
In view of the products offered by Audatex, it is easy to get an idea of the type of support that professionals in the sector can provide.
This company offers ten different tools, being the star product AudaPlus, the standard damage assessment solution, intended for experts.
Includes cars, motorcycles and light or heavy industrial vehicles.
In addition to the cost of the parts, it includes the repair times estimated by the manufacturer or the paint scales.
This tool is paid according to usage, for each valuation.
The highest cost is 5.75 euros, for customers who use it little, a maximum of ten times a month.
Then each insurance company, which performs thousands of audits, negotiates its price with Audatex.
Other products, such as AudaVIN, allow the total identification of a vehicle and the equipment with which it left the assembly line only with its frame number.
AudaGlass focuses on the moons of vehicles, and AudaSubastas is a service open to the professional sector on the Internet that allows bidding for vehicles declared total damage.
Its statistics service is very useful to identify trends, perform geodemographic analyses or know the deviations by brands or models.
You can study, for example, how many models of a particular brand have gone through the workshop due to breakdowns or how many have suffered serious injuries in a certain period.
Gt Motive is the only Spanish company dedicated to the development of this type of tools.
It sells, among others, Gt Estimate, which is also aimed at experts and also provides digital images, access to parts or prices and official times of the manufacturer.
Gt Motive is a company of the Einsa group founded in 1971 as a provider of services and solutions for the assessment of damage, breakdown or maintenance of the car.
The Gt Appraisal Guide is your historical benchmark product in the market.
They work with 24,000 users in workshops, 3,100 experts and 53 insurance companies.
Its turnover has grown at an annual rate of 20% in the last three years, and in 2008 it generated 10.8 million euros.
At the beginning of last year they began their process of internationalization, with the installation of an office in Paris.
Audatex was born in Germany in 1966 and established in Spain in 1979.
According to the company’s sources, 62% of its business is generated in Europe and the rest of the world, and the remaining 38%, in North and South America. They work with 900 insurance companies and 33,000 workshops, 3,000 of them in Spain.
