Cars with historical value can be unloaded even if they have been unloaded after a frantic process.
Workshop budget in four steps
With the Auda-Taller tool, the company Audatex ensures that the user gets a quote in just four steps: identify the vehicle, search for the spare part, create a quote and generate a budget.
Ease of use is an essential condition for these systems, especially to convince older professionals, who are more or less reluctant to use new management techniques.
The database includes 1,034 vehicles, which are 666 cars, 109 off-road vehicles, 137 motorcycles, 78 vans and 44 trucks.
Of course, to use it, you need a computer with an internet connection.
Once the model to be repaired is identified by its frame number, a real graphical image of the model in question appears, and then the necessary replacement is selected.
The user can include variables such as the price of labor, surcharges or discounts, and then can print the budget to deliver to the customer.
AudaTaller is not a valuation tool like AudaPlus, but rather a reference catalog.
The main difference between the two systems is that the workshop-oriented does not include estimated manpower times.
The cost of using this tool for the workshop is 350 euros per year, which the customer can finance.
Currently, the company Audatex is working to make these images three-dimensional.
